<article>
    <h1>Cases of nurses as&#xAD;sault&#xAD;ing charges</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201224/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-24"><time>2020-12-24</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Cara Wong</span>
    </section>

    <p>MARCH 6, 2019</p>
    <p>A nurse at Or­ange Val­ley Nurs­ing Home was jailed 12 weeks for punch­ing a res­i­dent with de­men­tia. Bernardo Jr Per­dido Ramos (left), 36, as­saulted the 77-year-old af­ter the man hit him once for “dis­turb­ing” him. Ramos re­tal­i­ated by punch­ing him four or five times in the face.</p>
    <p>JUNE 21, 2018</p>
    <p>A male staff nurse lost his tem­per with an in­tel­lec­tu­ally dis­abled pa­tient in the In­sti­tute of Men­tal Health and kicked him in the back at least four times. S. Ah­mad Shaz­aly S. Affindy (left), 27, was jailed six months for caus­ing hurt to the 56-year-old man, who is un­able to speak. The pa­tient had thrown a food tray at Ah­mad Shaz­aly’s col­league, and Ah­mad Shaz­aly was en­raged when the pa­tient re­fused to lis­ten to him.</p>
    <p>APRIL 18, 2016</p>
    <p>A Myan­mese nurse was jailed a year for as­sault­ing a pa­tient from the In­sti­tute of Men­tal Health. Aung Phyo Thu, 26, ad­mit­ted to punch­ing and kick­ing Mr Kong Ah Hoe, 56, a long-term pa­tient who suf­fers from schizophre­nia. Mr Kong was re­strained to the bed at the time and had dif­fi­cul­ties com­mu­ni­cat­ing. The at­tack caused him two rib frac­tures.</p>

